  "issues": [
    {
      "number": 3,
      "id": "I_kwDOKNEhZc59U4Nf",
      "title": "Considerations for AEADs",
      "url": "https://github.com/selfissued/draft-ietf-jose-fully-specified-algorithms/issues/3",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "OR13",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "In this rather long thread: https://mailarchive.ietf.org/arch/msg/jose/GcoCkOeg37tbFmZDkmtc3ExHVeU/\r\n\r\nWe discussed what fully specified means for HPKE and ECDH-ES+A128KW.\r\n\r\nWe considered solutions to binding the AEAD to the kdf, and how that is related to the current use of concatKDF, as described in https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7518#section-4.6.2\r\n\r\nNote that \"AlgorithmID\" is mixed in to the ECDH-ES KDF, so a fully specified algorithm would bind the resulting key similar to https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-housley-lamps-cms-cek-hkdf-sha256/",
      "createdAt": "2024-01-26T17:47:30Z",
      "updatedAt": "2024-01-26T17:47:30Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    }
